A 23-year-old man has been arrested for the kidnapping of two children, aged four and five, who were later found unharmed. JOHANNESBURG A 23-year-old suspect has been arrested for kidnapping two children in Protea Glen in Soweto, on Saturday. The two children aged four and five were unharmed, and the man s motive remains unknown. The police arrested the man late Saturday night when the parents alerted officials, that their children were missing. The police s Mpande Khoza, says police have launched an investigation -and urge residents to remain vigilant this festive season. There was no abuse on the children, but we have taken them to the doctor. During this festive time, they (parents) shouldn t allow children to roam around; more especially in busy places like malls. (Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)